ğŸ§  Common Transaction Problems Explained
Problem	Description	Example
Dirty Read	Reading uncommitted data from another transaction	T1 updates a row but hasnâ€™t committed â†’ T2 reads it
Non-Repeatable Read	Same query gives different results in same transaction	T1 reads a row, T2 updates it â†’ T1 reads again, value changed
Phantom Read	Same query returns different number of rows	T1 reads all rows, T2 inserts new row â†’ T1 reads again, extra row appears

âš™ï¸ How Isolation Levels Work in Java (Spring / JDBC)
âœ… Using Spring Boot / Spring Transactional
You can set isolation levels using @Transactional annotation:

@Transactional(isolation = Isolation.READ_COMMITTED)
public void updateAccount() {
    // business logic here
}
Supported Constants:

Isolation.READ_UNCOMMITTED
Isolation.READ_COMMITTED
Isolation.REPEATABLE_READ
Isolation.SERIALIZABLE

âœ… Default Isolation Level
Database	Default Isolation
