ğŸ’¡ Interview Summary Answer:
	â€œIsolation level defines how transactions interact with each other.
	Java supports four main levels â€” READ_UNCOMMITTED, READ_COMMITTED, REPEATABLE_READ, and SERIALIZABLE.
	As you go up, consistency increases but performance decreases.
	Typically, READ_COMMITTED is used as a balance between data safety and performance.â€
